<nav><span style="color: revert;font-family: inherit;font-size: 35px;font-style: inherit">What is a Post-Graduation Search Year Visa in Turkey? </nav>
<section id="h-turkiye-de-mezuniyet-sonrasi-arama-yili-visa-nedir" class="wp-block-heading">


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="purpose-of-the-search-year-visa">Purpose of the Search Year Visa</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The post-graduation search year visa is a program created to offer university graduates the opportunity to seek and work internationally. This visa provides graduates with the opportunity to put into practice the knowledge and skills they have gained during their studies and facilitates their participation in the world of work. Young people graduating from universities in Turkey can use this visa to use their diploma to meet potential employers. A search year visa offers the opportunity to not only look for a job, but also to have a cultural experience. Interacting with different cultures and people they meet while studying abroad provides a significant advantage in their career plans. Having the opportunity to see the dynamics of business life before entering the business life is at the very center of the post-graduation process.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="who-can-apply">Who Can Apply?</h3>


<p>There are some criteria to be eligible for this type of visa. First of all, you must have graduated from at least a four-year university program. In addition, those who have completed a four-year program with the Vertical Transfer Examination (DGS) can also apply for this visa. Thus, not only bachelor&#8217;s degree graduates but also young people who have completed other educational processes have the chance to take advantage of these opportunities. In order to apply for this visa, your degree must also be recognized (equivalence) by the country you are applying to. For example, it is important for students who want to look for a job in Germany to check in advance whether their university degree is recognized by Germany. </section>
<section id="h-Germany-is-search-visa" class="wp-block-heading">


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="germany-job-search-visa">Germany: Job Search Visa</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Germany is one of the countries with the most popular job search visa opportunity for Turkish university graduates. This visa is especially aimed at students studying in various fields such as engineering, medicine, arts and social sciences. Germany offers many opportunities for graduate students to integrate into the job market in the country.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="visa-duration-and-right">Visa Duration and Right</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The job search visa in Germany allows graduates a period of six months. During this time, they can reside in Germany to look for jobs and attend interviews. During the job search process, graduates can search for suitable positions, contact companies and take the necessary steps to achieve their career goals. If they receive a job offer within this six-month period, they can apply for a residence and work permit in Germany without returning to Turkey. With this type of visa in Germany, it is possible not only to look for a job, but also to take advantage of internship opportunities. During the duration of the visa, they can do a trial internship or work in temporary jobs. This allows them to gain experience and helps them to make professional contacts. A job search visa is an attractive option for young graduates as it offers a wide range of opportunities.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="certification-and-documents">Certification and Documents</h3>


<p>Those who will apply for a job search visa in Germany must first complete the equivalence procedures of their diplomas. The equivalence process varies depending on which department you are studying in and whether the university you graduated from is internationally recognized. This allows Turkish citizens who have studied in Germany to benefit from post-graduation job search permits. Documents required for visa application include a valid passport, CV, graduation diploma and equivalency certificate. In addition, at the time of visa application, you must open a blocked account that demonstrates your ability to cover living expenses in Germany. As of 2024, you will need to put a total amount of 6162 euros in the account. This financial requirement is an important step so that you can live safely when you go to Germany. </section>
<section id="h-UK-graduation-post-graduation-job-search-graduate-route" class="wp-block-heading">


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="uk-graduate-route-graduate-route">UK: Graduate Route (Graduate Route)</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The UK stands out with its &#8220;Graduate Route&#8221; program, which gives graduates the right to seek and work for two years. This visa offers an important opportunity especially for university students to realize their career goals after graduation. However, there are certain conditions for applying for this visa.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="visa-duration-and-conditions">Visa Duration and Conditions</h3>


<p>The duration of the Graduate Route visa allows you to look for a job or work full-time in any job after graduation. This is a very important opportunity for graduates because it offers support for graduates to start their <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/career-support-in-turkey/">career journey</a></p>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">. Students studying at well-known universities in the UK have the chance to look for a job with this visa when they graduate. However, the first requirement to apply for this visa is to have graduated from a recognized university in the UK. Graduates from universities in Turkey cannot apply for this visa.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-requirements">Application Requirements</h3>


<p>To apply for a Graduate Route visa, applicants must first provide proof of graduation from a UK university. In addition, it is important to prove the accuracy and validity of their graduation certificates. Visa applicants will have to pay a total of GBP 1,248 for bachelor&#8217;s and master&#8217;s degrees and GBP 1,872 for doctoral degrees. In addition, applications for graduates must be accompanied by certified documents issued by the educational institution in the UK. Having complete financial resources and submitting the right documents are key to applying for this visa. Considering these details, the Graduate Route visa for UK graduates offers a very advantageous option for graduates who take the right steps. </section>
<section id="h-diger-european-countries-firsat-karti-chancenkarte" class="wp-block-heading">


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="other-european-countries-chancenkarte-and-new-programs">Other European Countries: Chancenkarte and New Programs</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In other European countries, job search opportunities are also expanding. In particular, new points-based immigration programs such as Germany&#8217;s &#8220;Chancenkarte&#8221; (Opportunity Card), introduced in 2024 and beyond, offer great opportunities for qualified foreign labor. In this program, candidates who meet certain point criteria can obtain more flexible residence and job search opportunities. It is possible to apply by scoring points based on criteria such as education, age, work experience and language skills. The Opportunity Card is a particularly attractive option for Turkish students in higher education. The scoring system allows students to evaluate the opportunities that best suit their skills and experience, while at the same time increasing their chances of employment in Europe. With such systems, Germany aims to attract innovative labor.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="pointing-system">Pointing system</h3>


<p>Chancenkarte&#8217;s scoring system involves assessing candidates based on various criteria such as level of education, work experience and language skills. For example, completing higher education brings a certain number of points. In addition, your work experience and, if necessary, the languages you can speak also play an important role in the scoring. This system encourages the participation of talented individuals in the European workforce, aiming to ensure equal opportunities. This scoring system thus takes into account not only students&#8217; academic achievements, but also their potential in the world of work. In this way, students can express themselves in the best possible way and make the best candidates for the position they want. If you would like to learn more about this, you can check the <a style="color: #00c2ff !important;" href="https://tuerkei.diplo.de/tr-de/service/05-visaeinreise/2621828-2621828" target="_blank" rel="noopener">German Government</a></p>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">resources.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="general-visa-fee">General visa fee</h3>


<p>The general visa fee for the Opportunity Card is 75 euros. This fee is required to immediately validate the visa application and start processing the necessary documents. When applying for this type of visa for Turkish graduates, all documents must be properly prepared. Another point to be considered during the visa application process is the complete preparation of the documents required for the application. Passport, biometric passport photo and motivation letter are the key elements of the application process. In addition to job opportunities in Germany, similar practices are being developed in other European countries and these countries are looking for new ways to increase their workforce. It is of great importance that you take advantage of such opportunities to improve yourself and add experience in the international arena. </section>
<section id="h-is-search-visa-for-general-requirements-summary" class="wp-block-heading">


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="general-requirements-for-a-business-search-visa">General Requirements for a Business Search Visa</h2>


<p>Each country has its own requirements for applying for a job search visa. For example, to be eligible for a job search visa in Germany, you need to have graduated from at least a four-year university or a program approved by the Higher Education Council. In addition, you may need to have completed the recognition procedures first. However, it is also important for graduates applying for the Graduate Route in the UK to have graduated from a university in that country. In general, the required documents for both countries include a graduation diploma, passport and equivalence certificates. They also require proof of financial status; in Germany, this includes a requirement to have a certain amount in a blocked account. It is important to note that it is extremely important to meet these requirements for those who will apply for a job search visa. </section>
<section id="h-turkiye-graduates-for-general-evaluation" class="wp-block-heading">


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="general-evaluation-for-graduates-from-turkey">General Evaluation for Graduates from Turkey</h2>


<p>The most practical route for students graduating from Turkey is the German job search visa. It is critical that the graduation is recognized as equivalent by Germany and that the financial, language and paperwork requirements listed above are met. With its wide range of job opportunities, cultural diversity and developed workforce, Germany supports graduates to start a career abroad. The UK Graduate Route is only valid for Turkish citizens who have studied on home soil. Therefore, it is of great importance to take these details into consideration when considering studying abroad. It should be noted that other European countries may have similar application processes and requirements. </section>
<section id="h-final-steps-ready-to-take" class="wp-block-heading">


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="are-you-ready-to-take-the-final-steps">Are You Ready to Take the Final Steps?</h2>


<p>While the year visa for job search abroad offers a tremendous opportunity for you to make a new start in your career life, you need to find the right addresses for yourself in this process. Germany and the UK open their doors to a highly qualified workforce and are waiting for young graduates like you. Therefore, it is very important to decide which country you prefer and what documents you need to prepare. In addition to the opportunities, you will gain a new dimension in your career when you choose the right living space for you. By taking every step you need to take in this process, you can join the business world better equipped as an individual who has studied abroad. Remember, every new beginning is an opportunity. </section>
<section class="wp-block-heading">


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>


<h3>How many months is a German job search visa valid?</h3>
<p>The German job search visa is valid for six months after graduation.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">Can you start working immediately with this visa? </h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It is only possible to work on internships and temporary jobs with this visa; to start full-time employment you will need to apply for a residence permit after you have been offered a job.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-are-the-requirements-to-apply-for-the-graduate-route-in-the-uk">What are the requirements to apply for the Graduate Route in the UK?</h3>


<p>To apply for the Graduate Route, you must have graduated from a recognized university in the UK and provide the necessary documents.</p>
<h3 id="h-is-job-search-visa-infrastructure-available-in-other-European-countries">Is job search visa infrastructure available in other European countries?</h3>
