tostudy.com/en/part-time-work-permit-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/part-time-work-permit-in-turkey/","name":"Part-Time Work Permit in Turkey: Requirements","datePublished":"2026-03-18T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-18T14:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Part-Time Work Permit in Turkey: Requirements","keywords":"Part-time Work Permit","datePublished":"2026-03-18T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-18T14:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Visa and Immigration","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"What are the requirements for obtaining a part-time work permit in Turkey? Learn about the application process and details for international students!","name":"Part-Time Work Permit in Turkey: Requirements","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/part-time-work-permit-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/part-time-work-permit-in-turkey/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/part-time-work-permit-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In recent years, Turkey stands out with its growing educational opportunities and attractive options for international students. Among these opportunities, the part-time work permit, which is important for those continuing their education, stands out. The part-time work permit is a valuable support mechanism, especially for individuals with family obligations. In particular, employees who give birth or have young children can use this leave to better balance work and family life. For international students studying in Turkey, it is very important to have detailed information about the conditions and application process for a part-time work permit in Turkey in order to take the right steps in this process. Let&#8217;s dive deeper into this topic together!</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-is-a-part-time-work-permit-in-turkey">What is a Part-Time Work Permit in Turkey?</h2>


<p>In Turkey, part-time work leave is a special right granted to employees who give birth or adopt a child under the age of three. This leave allows these employees to work half of their weekly working hours. For example, if you work 45 hours per week in a full-time job, with part-time leave you have to work approximately 22.5 hours. This is a great opportunity for individuals who want to find a balanced path between family and work life. An important detail to be mentioned at this point is who can benefit from the part-time work permit. Part-time work leave applies not only to female employees who give birth, but also to male or female employees who adopt a child under the age of three. Thus, not only mothers but also fathers can benefit from this right. This practice is very important in terms of supporting family life and enabling parents to be more active in business life. According to <a href="https://www.tuik.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Turkey Statistical Institute</a> , the increasing number of employees giving birth in the country shows why part-time work leave is so important.</p>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="part-time-work-permit-conditions">Part-time Work Permit Conditions</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are some important conditions to be eligible for part-time work authorization. First of all, the applicant must have paid unemployment insurance premiums for at least 600 days in the three years prior to the date of birth or adoption. This is an important condition for employees to apply for state-subsidized part-time work leave. In addition, the application must be submitted no later than 30 days after the end of the maternity leave. Preparing the necessary documents and applying to İŞKUR during this period is critical for the process to proceed in a healthy way. In addition, the part-time work permit requires that you actually work half of the weekly working hours. For example, if you have a full-time job, you must work at least 22.5 hours per week to be eligible for part-time leave. This is determined within the framework of agreements with the employer and ensures that employees&#8217; social rights continue. Another detail to be aware of is who is eligible for part-time work leave; not only women but also men who adopt a child under the age of three can benefit from this right.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="half-time-working-allowance-and-rights-provided">Half-time Working Allowance and Rights Provided</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">People who are entitled to a half-work permit can receive a half-work allowance from the state. This allowance provides support for the periods when the employee is not actually working. The half-time allowance is an issue that should be considered together with the wage paid by the employer. The allowance for the hours not worked is regulated together with the wage to be paid by the employer. This helps employees to better manage their finances. In order to protect the social security rights of part-time workers, the government requires premium payments to be made to the Social Security Institution (SSI) at the minimum wage for the duration of the allowance. These payments are made as both employee and employer contributions. In other words, the part-time work permit allows employees to easily cover their social security premiums. In the long run, this situation also provides an advantage in the retirement process of individuals. Therefore, with a part-time work permit, it becomes possible to work and fulfill family responsibilities at the same time.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-process">Application Process</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The process for applying for a part-time work permit begins at the end of maternity leave following childbirth or adoption. In Turkey, maternity leave usually lasts for 112 days. After the end of this period, the applicant must prepare the necessary documents for the part-time work permit and apply to the nearest İŞKUR unit in person or through electronic channels. Preparation of the necessary documents is one of the most important steps of the application process. A half-work certificate must be obtained from the official website of İŞKUR. The application deadline is critical; it must be submitted no later than 30 days after the end of the maternity leave. Any delay during this period will be deducted from the total period of entitlement and reflected in the allowance accounts. Once the application is submitted, workers can start to benefit from the half-work permit and allowance after the approval process. Therefore, it is vital to pay attention to the timeframes specified in the application in order for the process to proceed smoothly.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="circumstances-where-the-half-time-work-allowance-is-cut-off">Circumstances where the half-time work allowance is cut off</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The half-time allowance can be withdrawn in certain circumstances, and being aware of this can be very helpful for employees in their financial planning. First of all, once the part-time work permit expires, the employee can no longer receive this allowance. Therefore, it is critical for individuals to be informed about the return to work process and their rights during this process. The half-work allowance will also stop when the employee returns to work or starts another job. In this case, it is important for the employee to accurately assess his or her current situation with the employer. In addition, the half-work allowance ends in the event of the death of the insured person or the death of the child. Such events are not only psychologically challenging, but can also affect financial means. Therefore, employees being prepared for such situations will help the process to be less stressful.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="relevant-legislation">Relevant Legislation</h2>


<p>With regard to partial work leave, various laws and regulations in Turkey protect the rights of employees. Article 74 of the Labor Law No. 4857 sets out the principles of half-work leave, while the Additional Article of the Unemployment Insurance Law No. 4447 provides information on the conditions and scope of the half-work allowance. These legislations provide details on how employees can benefit from the half-work permit and what they need to do in the process. These legislations aim to protect the rights of each individual, not just provide information. Within the framework of the laws, it is necessary to carry out the application process correctly and completely to avoid loss of rights. This constitutes an important step both in terms of protecting individual rights and ensuring social order.</p>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="consider-your-right-to-part-time-work-now">Consider Your Right to Part-Time Work Now</h2>


<p>Focusing on applying for a part-time work permit is very important for those who want to balance career and family life. If you have given birth or adopted a child under the age of three, find out as soon as possible about part-time work permits in Turkey. These applications, which seem like a long process, can actually be completed quickly with the right information. To apply now, check out <a style="color: #00c2ff !important;" href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/student-visa-application-process/">Turkey Student Visa: Application Process and Required</a><a style="color: #00c2ff !important;" href="https://roadtostudy.com/"> Documents</a></p>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In addition, the most important points to be considered during the application process are the completeness of the documents and the correct application date. Therefore, being informed about the process and applying quickly by completing the documentation in advance will provide a significant advantage.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="is-the-right-to-half-work-only-recognized-for-women">Is the right to half-work only recognized for women?</h3>


<p>No, male employees who adopt a child under the age of three are also eligible. This means that fathers as well as mothers can support their families.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Can I return to full-time work with half work permit?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-heading">Yes, if the employee and the employer agree, the employee can return to full-time work; however, in this case, the part-time allowance will cease. This transformation depends on the agreement of both the employee and the employer, within legal frameworks.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">If the child is born with a disability, does the half-work period change? </h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes, if a child is born with a disability, the part-time work permit applies for a total of 360 days. This is designed to be more responsive to the needs of people with disabilities.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-happens-if-there-is-a-delay-in-the-application">What happens if there is a delay in the application?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The time delayed in filing the application is deducted from the total period of entitlement. This emphasizes how important it is to apply on time.</p>



