anguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/visa-status-in-case-of-enrollment-suspension-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/visa-status-in-case-of-enrollment-suspension-in-turkey/","name":"Visa status in case of enrollment suspension in Turkey","datePublished":"2026-03-18T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-18T10:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Visa status in case of enrollment suspension in Turkey","keywords":"Visa status","datePublished":"2026-03-18T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-18T10:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Visa and Immigration","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Does freezing your enrollment affect your visa and residence status? Learn about the legal situation in Turkey and what you need to be aware of!","name":"Visa status in case of enrollment suspension in Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/visa-status-in-case-of-enrollment-suspension-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/visa-status-in-case-of-enrollment-suspension-in-turkey/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/visa-status-in-case-of-enrollment-suspension-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><p class="wp-block-paragraph" dir="ltr" data-pm-slice="1 1 []">Turkey offers a unique experience for international students with its high-quality educational opportunities and rich cultural heritage. However, one of the most important issues faced by international students wishing to study here is the student visa and its rights. A student visa not only offers the right to study, but also sets the legal boundaries for students who wish to pursue entrepreneurship. Don&#8217;t worry! In this article, we will explain step by step the possibilities of entrepreneurship with a student visa in Turkey, the legal regulations and the necessary documents. Acting with the right information is the first step to realizing your dreams. If you&#8217;re ready, let&#8217;s get started!</p></p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-is-registration-freeze">What is Registration Freeze?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">A registration freeze is defined as the temporary suspension of a student&#8217;s education based on a justified and valid reason, with the approval of the university administration. This process can be based on various reasons such as a health condition, personal reasons or academic difficulties. The important thing is that the freeze process is carried out officially and in accordance with the rules. Because if the registration freeze is not made, the student&#8217;s situation may cause legal problems. During the freeze, the student is not an active student, although he/she remains officially associated with his/her school. In other words, he/she cannot complete his/her credits by attending classes and this will systematically affect the student&#8217;s residence permit. It is important for international students pursuing higher education in Turkey to be informed about the legal procedures to be considered in this process.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="student-residence-permit-and-status">Student Residence Permit and Status</h2>


<p>Foreign students studying at higher education institutions in Turkey must obtain a student residence permit. This permit allows the student to reside legally in Turkey for the duration of their studies. You can find more comprehensive information about the residence permit on the <a style="color: #00c2ff !important" href="https://roadtostudy.com/ogrenci-ikamet-izni-formu/">Residence Permit in Turkey</a></p>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">page. A student residence permit gives the student the right to enter and exit the country without the need for a visa. Obtaining a student residence permit requires a specific process from start to finish and must be supported by various documents. Most universities provide detailed information on the documents required for your application. These documents usually include documents such as a university acceptance certificate, health insurance, financial qualification documents and copies of ID cards. All these steps are critical for you to maintain your legal status and continue your education in Turkey without using fake documents.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="registration-freeze-and-residence-permit">Registration Freeze and Residence Permit</h2>


<p>The suspension of enrollment has a direct impact on the status of the student&#8217;s residence permit. The residence permits of international students studying in Turkey are canceled during the enrollment freeze. Students who freeze their enrollment are obliged to leave Turkey within 15 days due to the termination of their enrollment or apply for another type of residence within this period. Otherwise, legal proceedings will be initiated and the student&#8217;s situation in Turkey may cause serious problems. In particular, the relevant Police Departments are regularly notified about students who have suspended their enrollment. In this context, it is very important for students to stay in contact with the school administration and submit the necessary documents in a timely manner. For more information about student residence permit in Turkey, please visit <a style="color: #00c2ff !important;" href="https://roadtostudy.com/ogrenci-ikamet-izni-yenileme/">Student Residence Permit Renewal Process in Turkey</a></p>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="visa-status-and-re-entry-to-turkey">Visa Status and Re-entry to Turkey</h2>


<p>The visa status of students who have frozen their enrollment is a critical issue when re-entering Turkey. If a student takes a leave of absence from school for less than a year, he/she can enter Turkey on a tourist visa. However, there is an important point in this process: The student residence permit will be canceled and the student will need to reapply for a student residence permit. This is a legal obligation for students and must be followed carefully. If a student suspends enrollment for more than one year, he/she must obtain a new student visa upon return to Turkey. This is due to the revocation of existing student residence permits. These preparations for returning to Turkey are critical for the student to continue his/her education and are an important step that students should pay attention to. For up-to-date information on both visa and residence permit processes, it is useful to visit official sources, such as the website of the <a style="color: #00c2ff !important;" href="https://www.icisleri.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">T.R. Ministry of Interior</a></p>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="school-registration-and-graduation">School Registration and Graduation</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The situation of foreign students who win a school but do not enroll within the specified period is of critical importance in the education system in Turkey. The school administration notifies the relevant police departments about the non-registration of these students. As a result, these students lose their right to obtain a residence permit. In other words, even if they are admitted to school, they cannot legally stay in Turkey because they have not completed the necessary registration processes. After graduation, students&#8217; student residence permits are canceled. If a graduating student wishes to stay in Turkey, it will not be possible without applying for another type of residence permit. Therefore, it is important for graduating students to take timely steps to secure a valid residence permit on Turkish territory, given their legal status. Those who wish to work or otherwise stay in Turkey after graduation must apply for a new residence permit.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="relevant-legal-processes-and-change-of-residence-type">Relevant Legal Processes and Change of Residence Type</h2>


<p>Foreign students must leave Turkey within 15 days if they freeze or cancel their enrollment with their school. Alternatively, they must apply for another type of residence permit, such as a short-term residence permit, within this period. Otherwise, students who are not legally allowed to stay in Turkey may be considered as fugitives. This can result in serious sanctions, both deportation and administrative fines. It is important for students to be careful in terms of following the current processes in cases such as registration suspension or dismissal. Following the official procedures is the most important step in preventing legal problems. Submitting the required documents in full and on time plays a critical role for students to maintain their legal status. In this context, you can get support from the <a style="color: #00c2ff !important;" href="https://www.icisleri.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">T.C. Ministry of Interior</a> website for information on the relevant legal processes.</p>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="visa-and-residence-status-in-case-of-registration-freeze">Visa and Residence Status in case of Registration Freeze</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The above processes and rules are extremely important for foreign students studying in Turkey to maintain their legal status. Since a registration freeze means the automatic cancellation of the student&#8217;s residence permit, it is necessary to take a careful and proactive approach. It is especially important to take the necessary steps within the specified 15-day period and ensure that the official processes are followed.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="does-a-registration-freeze-affect-a-student-visa">Does a registration freeze affect a student visa?</h3>


<p>Yes, the student residence permit is canceled in case of a registration freeze. It is necessary to leave Turkey or apply for another residence permit.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Can one re-enter with a tourist visa while holding a residence permit?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-heading">For a registration suspension of less than one year, yes, but for more than one year a new student visa is required.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">Can you stay in Turkey during the registration freeze? </h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">No, you cannot stay in Turkey as the residence permit has been canceled. Within 15 days, you must exit or apply for another type of residence permit.</p>



