tudy in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/health-report-for-residence-permit-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/health-report-for-residence-permit-in-turkey/","name":"Health Report for Residence Permit in Turkey: Where and How to Get it?","datePublished":"2026-03-16T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-16T14:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Health Report for Residence Permit in Turkey: Where and How to Get it?","keywords":"Health Report","datePublished":"2026-03-16T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-16T14:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Visa and Immigration","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Turkey offers a unique experience for international students with its high-quality educational opportunities and rich cultural diversity. Foreign students who","name":"Health Report for Residence Permit in Turkey: Where and How to Get it?","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/health-report-for-residence-permit-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/health-report-for-residence-permit-in-turkey/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/health-report-for-residence-permit-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p><span style="font-size: inherit; font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, BlinkMacSystemFont, ''Segoe UI'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, ''Apple Color Emoji'', ''Segoe UI Emoji'', ''Segoe UI Symbol'';">Turkey offers a unique experience for international students with its high-quality educational opportunities and rich cultural diversity. Foreign students who wish to study in Turkey face visa and residence permit processes. An important step in these processes is obtaining a health report. The health report is required to protect public health and verify that the applicant meets the required health criteria. This report is a critical stage, especially for first-time residence permit applicants or students seeking a change of status.</span></p>
<div class="wp-block-paragraph">
<p dir="ltr">In this article, we will explain step by step how to get a medical report for a residence permit in Turkey, where to obtain it and all the details about the process. Acting with the right information will help you minimize potential problems during the application process. If you are ready, let&#8217;s examine in detail the situations where a medical report is required and how to get it!</p>
</div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-is-a-health-report-for-residence-permit-in-turkey">What is a Health Report for Residence Permit in Turkey?</h2>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph">Foreigners who wish to obtain a residence permit in Turkey must obtain a medical report in some cases. The importance of the medical report depends on the type and purpose of the permit applied for. For example, for a person who wants to apply for a <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/long-term-residence-permit/">long-term residence permit</a>, the health status is an important part of the process. This indicates whether the applicant is medically fit and is a constitutional requirement of security for him or herself and his or her environment. Another example is foreigners aiming to find a job in Turkey. Those who want to work in high-risk jobs are often required to submit a health report. This report is mandatory for the safety of the employer and to ensure that they are not in a favored position in the workplace. Therefore, the importance of obtaining this report should not be underestimated, especially for first-time residence permit applicants.</div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="health-report-requested-application-situations">Health Report Requested Application Situations</h2>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph"> The request for a medical certificate is not limited to a few important situations. Long-term residence permit applications, for foreigners applying for marriage in Turkey, and for those working in certain employment positions are among the most common situations where a health certificate is required. Citizens wishing to obtain a long-term residence permit must prove that they do not pose any health risks. At the same time, foreigners wishing to marry in Turkey must submit a medical report in order to complete the marriage procedures. This report, which usually includes some medical screening, is requested to certify that the parties are in good health for marriage. If you plan to work in a high-risk job, you may need to prove your medical condition. This increases the necessity of a health report. </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="where-to-get-a-health-report-in-turkey">Where to Get a Health Report in Turkey</h2>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph">It is very important to choose the right hospitals to obtain a medical report. A health report can only be obtained from full-fledged public hospitals or private hospitals authorized to issue reports. It is important to note that not all public hospitals in Turkey have this authorization. Therefore, first checking which hospitals are authorized to issue medical reports will speed up the application process. It is also important to know that family physicians cannot issue full-fledged reports required for official applications such as residence permits. Therefore, considering these situations and choosing the right hospital will minimize the problems that may arise during the process of obtaining a health report. The documents required to obtain a health report include an identity document, two photographs and application documents. For more information on official health authorities and related resources in Turkey, visit the website of <a style="color: #00c2ff !important;" href="https://www.goc.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Göç İdaresi</a>.</div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="documents-required-for-application">Documents Required for Application</h2>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph"> Some documents are usually required to obtain a health report. These documents include a passport or valid identity document, two passport size photographs, a report application form and a health report fee. The report application form can be provided by the hospital or you can obtain it yourself in advance. Another important point to note is that the medical report should not exceed 30 days from the date of application; this is important to keep the report up-to-date. In particular, the cost of the report may vary depending on the hospital and the scope of the report. Public hospitals generally charge lower fees, while private hospitals may set higher prices. Having information about the uncertainties you may encounter during the process of obtaining a health report will make your application process more manageable. </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-the-health-report-process-works">How the Health Report Process Works</h2>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph"> The process of obtaining a health report can go quite smoothly if you follow the right steps. First, you need to make an appointment at an authorized public hospital or an approved private hospital. You can usually make the appointment through hospital websites or by phone. When making an appointment, it is useful to ask for information about which documents you need to take with you. When you go to the hospital, you need to submit your application with your identity document and other necessary documents. After the necessary examinations and medical tests, a medical doctor will prepare your medical report. The report becomes valid with the doctor&#8217;s signature and stamp. One detail you should pay attention to in this process is to remember to take a copy of the report for your own records. The original report is the document to be submitted with the residence permit application. </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="validity-period-and-content-of-health-report">Validity Period and Content of Health Report</h2>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph"> The validity of the medical certificate is limited to a maximum of 30 days from the date of issue. This is due to the requirement to present an up-to-date health status at the time of application. The report contains the doctor&#8217;s signature and stamp as well as your medical findings regarding the diagnosis. Additional forms, if required, must also be part of the report. This may be requested in particular to document certain medical conditions. It would also be useful to have additional documents to avoid any misunderstandings or problems with the health status during the preparation of the report. </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Which hospitals issue medical reports?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">All full-fledged state hospitals and private hospitals authorized to issue reports can issue a health report. Family physicians are not qualified and are not considered valid for official applications. If you are having difficulty finding the right hospitals, you can ask the health directorate in your province to help you.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="do-i-need-an-appointment-to-get-a-medical-report">Do I need an appointment to get a medical report?</h3>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes, most hospitals provide services by appointment, especially in big cities. Going without an appointment can lead to long waiting times. Also, do not forget to ask the authorities at the hospital about which documents you need to take with you during the appointment.</div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-much-does-a-medical-report-cost">How much does a medical report cost?</h3>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph"> Fees vary depending on the hospital and the scope of the report. Public hospitals usually charge lower fees, while private hospitals may charge higher prices. To get a clearer answer to this question, it is useful to call the hospital you will go to. </div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="is-a-health-report-mandatory-for-a-residence-permit">Is a health report mandatory for a residence permit?</h3>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph"> Some types of residence permits require a medical report, especially for initial applications or for certain status transfers. However, for short-term residence permit applications, this requirement may vary depending on the type of application. For details, I recommend you to visit <a style="color: #00c2ff !important" href="https://www.goc.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Migration Administration</a>. </div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-other-documents-are-required-besides-the-medical-report">What other documents are required besides the medical report?</h3>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph"> The application form, passport, proof of address, proof of accommodation (lease contract, hotel registration, etc.), biometric photograph and documents showing your living situation, if any, are usually required for a residence permit application. Missing any document during the application process may cause the process to be prolonged, so take care to prepare your documents meticulously. </div>', "wp_published_at" = '2026-03-16T11:00:00Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T18:57:58Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'health-report-for-residence-permit-in-turkey';
