with our step-by-step guide!","name":"How to Open Water, Gas and Electricity Subscriptions","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/water-gas-and-electricity-subscriptions/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/water-gas-and-electricity-subscriptions/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/how-to-open-water-gas-and-electricity-subscriptions-in-turkiye-1.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/water-gas-and-electricity-subscriptions/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-is-water-gas-and-electricity-subscription-in-turkey">What is Water, Gas and Electricity Subscription in Turkey?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Subscriptions for water, gas and electricity are the official procedures required for a home or business to benefit from these essential services. These subscriptions are necessary for the continuous supply of water, gas and electricity in your living space. There are different suppliers for each service in Turkey and subscription transactions are carried out according to the procedures determined by these suppliers.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="subscription-process-for-international-students">Subscription Process for International Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">International students should follow certain steps to open their water, gas and electricity subscriptions when they arrive in Turkey. Here are the steps to follow in this process:</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">1. <strong>Determining a Residential Address</strong>: First, you need to determine the address where you will reside. You can choose an accommodation option such as a rented apartment or a dormitory.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">2. <strong>Collect the Necessary Documents</strong>: You should prepare the necessary documents for subscription procedures. These documents usually include identification, proof of residence, and a rental agreement.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">3. <strong>Applying</strong>: You must apply to your water, gas and electricity suppliers. This can usually be done online or by visiting the relevant supplier&#8217;s office.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">4. <strong>Subscription Approval</strong>: Once your application has been approved, you can start using your services. Subscription procedures are usually completed within 1-2 weeks.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">How to pay a water bill in Turkey?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, paying a <strong>water bill (su faturası)</strong> is simple and can be done in several ways — both online and offline. Here’s a clear breakdown for locals and international residents:</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">1. Through Your Municipality’s Official Website</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Each city has its own water authority (called <em>Su ve Kanalizasyon İdaresi</em>).<br>Examples:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><a href="https://iski.istanbul/" data-type="link" data-id="https://iski.istanbul/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">İSKİ</a> (İstanbul)</li>



<li><a href="https://iski.istanbul/" data-type="link" data-id="https://iski.istanbul/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ASKİ</a> (Ankara)</li>



<li><a href="https://www.izsu.gov.tr/tr/Anasayfa" data-type="link" data-id="https://www.izsu.gov.tr/tr/Anasayfa" target="_blank" rel="noopener">İZSU</a> (İzmir)</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Create an account using your <strong>subscriber number (abone numarası)</strong> — written on your bill.</li>



<li>Check your current balance.</li>



<li>Pay securely by <strong>credit or debit card</strong>.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">2. At Banks</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Almost all Turkish banks accept utility payments:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>You can pay <strong>in person</strong> at the branch or via <strong>ATM</strong>.</li>



<li>Use <strong>online banking</strong> or <strong>mobile apps</strong> (Ziraat Bankası, Garanti BBVA, İşbank, Yapı Kredi, etc.).</li>



<li>Many banks let you <strong>set up automatic payments</strong> (<em>otomatik ödeme talimatı</em>) so your bill is paid monthly from your account.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">3. Using Mobile Apps</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Popular apps like:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong><a href="https://www.turkiye.gov.tr/" data-type="link" data-id="https://www.turkiye.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">e-Devlet</a></strong> → allows viewing and paying bills for many regions.</li>



<li><strong>TURKCELL Paycell</strong>, <strong>Papara</strong>, <strong>Enpara</strong>, <strong>Hepsipay</strong>, or <strong>Trendyol Cüzdan</strong> — all allow easy digital payments for registered users.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">4. At PTT Offices or Payment Centers</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can also pay:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>At <strong>PTT (Post Office)</strong> branches nationwide.</li>



<li>At <strong>authorized bill payment centers</strong> (<em>fatura ödeme merkezi</em>) — common in neighborhoods.<br>Just bring your <strong>subscriber number or last bill</strong> and pay in cash or card.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">5. For Tenants or New Residents</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you’ve just moved in:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Visit your local water authority office (e.g., İSKİ, ASKİ) with your <strong>rental contract</strong> and <strong>ID/<a href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/what-to-do-in-case-of-passport-loss-in-turkey/" data-type="post" data-id="10557">passport</a></strong> to register the subscription under your name.</li>



<li>This ensures future bills are sent to you and not the previous tenant.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="required-documents-and-conditions-whats-required-for-subscription">Required Documents and Conditions: What&#8217;s Required for Subscription?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The documents required to open a water, gas and electricity subscription in Turkey may vary depending on the supplier and region of residence. However, the following documents are generally required:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Identity Document</strong>: Passport or Republic of Turkey identity card.</li>



<li><strong>Document of Residence</strong>: A document proving the address of the place you are renting.</li>



<li><strong>Rental Agreement</strong>: If you live in a rented house, the <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/processes-for-residential-rental-in-turkey/" data-type="post" data-id="7154">rental agreement</a> you have with the landlord.</li>



<li><strong>Previous Subscription Information</strong>: Old subscription information, if any.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Complete and accurate submission of these documents will ensure that subscription transactions are completed quickly.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="water-gas-and-electricity-subscription-fees-in-turkey-how-much-will-you-pay">Water, Gas and Electricity Subscription Fees in Turkey: How Much Will You Pay?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Subscription fees may vary depending on the supplier and region. In general, water, gas and electricity subscription fees in Turkey are as follows:</p>


<p><strong>Water Fees:</strong> On average, <strong data-start="117" data-end="136">1.25 &#8211; 3.75 USD</strong> is paid for monthly water consumption.<br data-start="169" data-end="172" /><strong>Gas Fees:</strong> As gas consumption increases during the winter months, the average monthly gas fee ranges from <strong data-start="254" data-end="273">2.50 &#8211; 7.50 USD</strong>.<br data-start="297" data-end="300" /><strong>Electricity Fees</strong>: On average, <strong data-start="358" data-end="377">2.50 &#8211; 5.00 USD</strong></p>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">is paid for monthly electricity consumption.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These prices may vary depending on the service used and the amount of consumption.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="experiences-of-opening-a-subscription-in-turkey-tips-from-international-students">Experiences of Opening a Subscription in Turkey: Tips from International Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">International students may face some difficulties in the process of opening a subscription in Turkey. Here are some tips from students who shared their experiences in this process:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Learn the Local Language</strong>: Knowing Turkish makes it easier to communicate in subscription procedures. Learning basic words can speed up the process.</li>



<li><strong>Get Support from Education Counselors</strong>: You can ask for help from your university&#8217;s international office or education counselors. They can provide information about the subscription process.</li>



<li><strong>Communicate with Other Students</strong>: Connect with other international students going through the same process and learn from their experiences.</li>



<li><strong>Apply on Time</strong>: Prepare the documents required for subscription procedures on time and submit your application early. This will help you get your services faster.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="start-your-water-gas-and-electricity-connections-easily">Start Your Water, Gas and Electricity Connections Easily!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Taking out water, gas and electricity subscriptions in Turkey is an important step to make life easier for international students. The documents, conditions and tips to be considered in this process will help students to make their subscription process more smoothly. Studying and living in Turkey is not only an academic experience but also a cultural journey. With the right information and planning, you can be successful in this process. Remember, the comfort of your life in Turkey starts with the provision of these basic services.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What documents are required to open a water, gas and electricity subscription in Turkey?</h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In order to open a water, gas and electricity subscription, an identity document, proof of residence, rental agreement and previous subscription information are required.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-long-does-the-subscription-process-take">How long does the subscription process take?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Subscription procedures are usually completed within 1-2 weeks. However, this period may vary depending on the supplier and the volume of applications.</p>


<h3>How many USD for electricity, water and natural gas subscriptions?</h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Electricity subscription security fee is approximately <span class="math-inline"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="mord">16,13</span></span></span></span></span> USD, the average water subscription fee is <span class="math-inline"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="mord">31,25</span></span></span></span></span> USD and the natural gas security fee is approximately <span class="math-inline"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="mord">75,88</span></span></span></span></span> USD.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-is-required-for-electricity-and-water-subscription">What is required for electricity and water subscription?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For electricity and water subscriptions, an identity document (T.R. ID card), proof of ownership (title deed or lease contract), Compulsory Earthquake Insurance (DASK) policy and an old invoice or meter number, if available, are usually required. Additional documents may be requested according to the institution to apply.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="can-electricity-water-and-natural-gas-be-opened-from-e-government">Can electricity, water and natural gas be opened from e-government?</h3>


<p>Yes, electricity, water and natural gas subscription applications can be made easily through the e-Government Gateway. You can complete your application by logging in to <a href="https://www.turkiye.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">turkiye.gov.tr</a> with your T.R. ID number and password, selecting the &#8220;New Subscription Application&#8221; service of the relevant institution and following the steps.</p>


