<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-long-does-the-subscription-process-take">How long does the subscription process take?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Subscription procedures are usually completed within 1-2 weeks. However, this period may vary depending on the supplier and the volume of applications.</p>


<h3>How many USD for electricity, water and natural gas subscriptions?</h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Electricity subscription security fee is approximately <span class="math-inline"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="mord">16,13</span></span></span></span></span> USD, the average water subscription fee is <span class="math-inline"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="mord">31,25</span></span></span></span></span> USD and the natural gas security fee is approximately <span class="math-inline"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="mord">75,88</span></span></span></span></span> USD.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-is-required-for-electricity-and-water-subscription">What is required for electricity and water subscription?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For electricity and water subscriptions, an identity document (T.R. ID card), proof of ownership (title deed or lease contract), Compulsory Earthquake Insurance (DASK) policy and an old invoice or meter number, if available, are usually required. Additional documents may be requested according to the institution to apply.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="can-electricity-water-and-natural-gas-be-opened-from-e-government">Can electricity, water and natural gas be opened from e-government?</h3>


