pet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/clothing-and-personal-care-costs-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/clothing-and-personal-care-costs-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/clothing-and-personal-care-costs-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey offers a rich market for clothing and personal care products for both local and international students. In this article, we will discuss the cost of clothing and personal care products in Turkey, budget-friendly options, shopping considerations, how to take advantage of seasonal discounts and cultural influences in Turkey.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="prices-of-clothing-and-personal-care-products-in-turkey-how-much-should-students-spend">Prices of Clothing and Personal Care Products in Turkey: How Much Should Students Spend?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The amount spent on clothing and personal care products in Turkey varies depending on students&#8217; lifestyles and preferred brands. Below you will find a list of general price ranges:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong data-start="89" data-end="108">Clothing Items:</strong><br>T-shirt: 2.5-7.5 USD<br>Pants: 5-15 USD<br>Jacket: 7.5-20 USD<br>Shoes: 6.25-17.5 USD</li>



<li><strong data-start="201" data-end="228">Personal Care Products:</strong><br>Shampoo: USD 0.75-2.5<br>Hair conditioner: USD 0.75-2.5<br>Skin cream: 1.25-5 USD<br>Perfume: 2.5-12.5 USD</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can also benefit from our article <a title="Costs of Money Transfer and Foreign Exchange Transactions in Turkey" href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Costs of Money Transfer and Foreign Exchange Transactions in Turkey</a>.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="budget-friendly-clothing-and-personal-care-products-options-for-students">Budget Friendly Clothing and Personal Care Products Options for Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Budget-friendly shopping for students is quite possible in Turkey. Here are some suggestions:</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Local Brands:</strong> Many local brands in Turkey offer quality products at affordable prices. These brands include popular choices such as LC Waikiki, Koton and Mavi.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Second Hand Stores:</strong> Second hand clothing stores offer both an economical and environmentally friendly shopping alternative. In these stores, it is possible to find quality and gently used products.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Online Shopping:</strong> Online platforms such as <a href="http://www.trendyol.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Trendyol</a>, <a href="https://www.hepsiburada.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hepsiburada</a> offer frequent discounts and campaigns, allowing students to shop within their budget.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Seasonal Discounts:</strong> Summer and winter seasonal discounts offer great savings opportunities for students. During these periods, many stores offer discounts of up to 50%.</p>



