iye.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/ways-to-secure-accommodation-in-turkiye.webp","width":"1168","height":"880","caption":"International student securing accommodation in Turkey","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/securing-accommodation-tips-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/securing-accommodation-tips-in-turkey/","name":"Tips for Securing Accommodation in Turkey","datePublished":"2025-08-14T13:00:22+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:46:32+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/ways-to-secure-accommodation-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Tips for Securing Accommodation in Turkey","keywords":"Securing Accommodation","datePublished":"2025-08-14T13:00:22+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:46:32+03:00","articleSection":"Cost of Living and Accommodation","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Discover practical tips for securing accommodation in Turkey. Book quickly and secure your holiday!","name":"Tips for Securing Accommodation in Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/securing-accommodation-tips-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/securing-accommodation-tips-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/ways-to-secure-accommodation-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/securing-accommodation-tips-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are an international student planning to study in Turkey, finding a safe and comfortable accommodation should be one of your top priorities. While a wrong choice can lead to both financial and moral problems, a right decision can make your whole education life easier.<br data-start="488" data-end="491">So, how to avoid scams in Turkey? How should contracts be structured? Which platforms can you trust? In this post, we&#8217;ll share the accommodation assurance tips and steps you need to know to make your accommodation process smooth and safe.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="accommodation-options-in-turkey-which-type-of-accommodation-to-prefer">Accommodation Options in Turkey: Which Type of Accommodation to Prefer?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Student accommodation options in Turkey are quite diverse. There are different alternatives according to students&#8217; needs and budgets. Here are the most common types of accommodation:</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">1. <strong>Student Dormitories</strong>: Usually located near universities, dormitories offer accommodation to students at affordable prices. Dormitories usually include services such as food, internet and cleaning.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">2. <strong>Shared Apartments</strong>: Several students can get together and rent an apartment. This option offers more space and privacy and the advantage of sharing costs.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">3. <strong>Private Apartments</strong>: For those who want to stay alone or with a family, private apartments usually offer more comfort but at a higher cost.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">4. <strong>Hostels</strong>: Another option for short-term stays is guesthouses. They are usually more affordable.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="practical-examples">Practical Examples</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Student Dormitories</strong>: Dormitories close to Boğaziçi University in Istanbul, with prices ranging from 150-200 USD per month.</li>



<li><strong>Shared Apartments</strong>: In Ankara, 3-4 students can get together and rent an apartment for between 400-600 USD.</li>



<li><strong>Private Apartments</strong>: Renting a studio apartment in Izmir can cost between 300-500 USD per month.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can also benefit from our article <a title="Accommodation Options for International Students in Turkey" href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Housing Options for International Students in Turkey</a>.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-to-do-in-the-accommodation-reservation-process">What to Do in the Accommodation Reservation Process</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are some important steps to consider when booking accommodation:</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">1. <strong>Do Your Research</strong>: Research different accommodation options and compare prices and services.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">2. <strong>Early Booking</strong>: Especially in the summer months and during university opening periods, accommodation fills up quickly. You can find better prices and options by booking early.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">3. <strong>Use Trusted Sources</strong>: When booking, use trusted websites or sources recommended by your university.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">4. <strong>Read the Contract</strong>: Read the rental agreement carefully and ask for clarification if you do not understand it.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">5. <strong>Check Payment Terms</strong>: Familiarize yourself with payment terms and cancellation policies in advance.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can also check out <a title="Safe Accommodation Options for Female Students in Turkey" href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Safe Accommodation Options for Female Students in Turkey</a>.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="affordable-accommodation-tips-for-international-students">Affordable Accommodation Tips for International Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Finding affordable accommodation for international students can sometimes be challenging. Here are some tips to consider:</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">1. <strong>Contact Local Students</strong>: Local students can provide useful information about accommodation and inform you about affordable options.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">2. <strong>Use Social Media</strong>: Facebook groups or other social media platforms can be a useful resource for students looking for accommodation.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">3. <strong>Use University Facilities</strong>: Many universities offer special accommodation services for international students. Be sure to take advantage of these services.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">4. <strong>Search for Scholarships and Discounts</strong>: Some dormitories and accommodation facilities offer special discounts or scholarships to students.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="practical-examples">Practical Examples</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Communicate with Local Students</strong>: You can communicate with local students through your university&#8217;s student clubs or social media groups.</li>



<li><strong>University Facilities</strong>: For example, Istanbul Technical University offers accommodation services for international students.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="reliable-sources-for-accommodation-in-turkey">Reliable Sources for Accommodation in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It is very important to use reliable sources when booking accommodation in Turkey. Here are some reliable sources you should consider:</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">1. <strong>University Official Websites</strong>: Official university websites provide the most up-to-date information about accommodation options for students.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">2. <strong>Online Booking Sites</strong>: Platforms such as <a href="https://www.airbnb.com.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Airbnb</a>, <a href="http://www.booking.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Booking.com</a> offer a wide range of accommodation and allow you to compare prices.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">3. <strong>Local Student Associations</strong>: Local student associations can provide information and support on accommodation.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">4. <strong>Social Media Groups</strong>: Student groups on Facebook and other social media platforms can be useful for finding accommodation.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="local-recommendations-for-a-safe-and-comfortable-stay">Local Recommendations for a Safe and Comfortable Stay</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It is important to pay attention to local advice to ensure a safe and comfortable experience during your stay. Here are some tips to consider:</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">1. <strong>Know the Neighborhood</strong>: Investigate the safety of the area where you will be staying. Get information from the locals to find out which areas are safer.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">2. <strong>Check Transportation</strong>: Make sure your accommodation is close to public transportation. This will make your daily life easier.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">3. <strong>Take Security Measures</strong>: Check the security measures in your accommodation. Lockable doors and security cameras are important.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">4. <strong>Listen to Local Advice</strong>: Advice from locals or other students can be useful for a safe and comfortable stay.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="practical-examples">Practical Examples</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Knowing the Neighborhood</strong>: Staying in popular and safe neighborhoods in Istanbul, such as Kadikoy, also contributes positively to your social life.</li>



<li><strong>Transportation Facilities</strong>: For example, if your accommodation in Izmir is close to the metro or bus stops, it will make transportation easier.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="take-action-for-safe-accommodation">Take Action for Safe Accommodation!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey is a country that offers educational opportunities and cultural richness for international students. Accommodation is one of the most important parts of this experience. Finding the right accommodation option can positively impact both your academic and social life. With the tips and practical examples mentioned above, you can secure your accommodation in Turkey and enjoy this unique experience.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-is-the-language-of-instruction-at-universities-in-turkey">What is the language of instruction at universities in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Many universities in Turkey offer education in English and Turkish. Which language you study depends on the program you choose.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-is-the-cost-of-living-in-turkey">How is the cost of living in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The cost of living in Turkey varies from city to city, but it is generally possible to live on a budget of 200-300 USD.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-documents-are-required-to-obtain-a-student-visa">What documents are required to obtain a student visa?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">To obtain a student visa, you will need an acceptance letter, passport, health insurance and documents showing your financial situation.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="are-there-any-internship-opportunities-in-turkey">Are there any internship opportunities in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes, many universities in Turkey offer internship opportunities to their students. These opportunities are important for shaping your career.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-are-the-accommodation-options-in-turkey">What are the accommodation options in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are various accommodation options for students. There are alternatives such as dormitories, private apartments and shared accommodation. Dormitory prices usually range between 100-150 USD.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">With this information you can better understand the accommodation opportunities in Turkey and enjoy this unique experience. At RoadToStudy, we are happy to support you in your study life in Turkey.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-08-14T10:00:22Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T18:46:32Z', "featured_image" = '{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/ways-to-secure-accommodation-in-turkiye.webp","alt":"International student securing accommodation in Turkey","title":"ways-to-secure-accommodation-in-turkiye"}' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'securing-accommodation-tips-in-turkey';
